    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. But what about the people who live on the outskirts and rely on driving to get to their jobs in the city? If these policies are \"undeniably critical,\" how do we address the argument that they just end up being a regressive tax that punishes the working class for a problem they didn't create?",
